The Herald Sports Reporter ZIMBABWE lost their fourth consecutive match at the ongoing International Handball Federation Trophy continental phase on Thursday when they went down to Madagascar in Brazzaville, Congo. They were defeated 38-30 by Madagascar. They are yet to win a match at the continental event having already lost to Congo, Guinea, and Nigeria. Zimbabwe secured a spot at the tournament last October when they emerged as winners of the regional competition that was serving as a qualifier. Their last match is against Rwanda today.